\section{Getting Rare Elements}
It may be possible to send metal ``scoops'' with very high
melting points through the Suns atmosphere to pick up valuable 
rare materials e.g. radioactive elements with short half lifes.
These scoops can be emptied out once they have been passed through
the other side of the suns atmosphere.
