\chapter{Open letter to George W. Bush, Al Jizera,
Gerry Adams, Oprah Winfrey, Pope Benedict, Saddam Hussein,
Tom Cruise, John Travolta \& the Jews,
my twopence worth on politics}
\paragraph
\noindent
\textit{\\}
Hi all,\\
\paragraph
\noindent
Scientology I believe is a company posing as a religion to avoid tax 
started by a science fiction writer \& has sued people
for saying this, religions don't sue people for slander.
\paragraph
\noindent
I am not Anti American or anyone else for that matter.
I've met nice people from all walks of life.
I take a lot of potshots at George W. in this letter
it's nothing personal, I just think his policies are
very seriously flawed, I strongly suspect he has his own
hidden agendas \& any sane person is very
likely to agree with me.
\paragraph
\noindent
George W. wasn't elected president of America for his
first term in office, certain demographic groups
in Florida who voted for Al Gore were discounted.
George was helped by his brother Jeb, the Governor
of Florida. John Ellis first cousin of George W. Bush
ran Fox News Network's ``decision desk'' during
the 2000 election \& Fox was the first to
name Bush the winner.  
\paragraph
\noindent
Saddam Hussein has survived 30 coup attempts,
he's a survivor,
\& will kill his own family if they go against him,
is George W. Bush better?
The Bushs love Oil, they go to war for it.
Saddam may need to be the way he is to run a
messed up country like Iraq, however, but he could
certainly take a few lessons from Kuwait.
Saddam has the guts to shoot a man himself,
the Bushs just get others to do their dirty work,
American \& British soldiers just following orders, wake up!,
Saddam deserves more respect than Bush does,
he will dirty his own hands.
History is complicated if you examine it
there is a lot of double dealing 
\& incestuous behavior going on, America
has a habit of doing whatever serves it's
best interest moment to moment.
In the 1980's Donald Rumsfeld you shook Saddam's hand,
opened an American Embassy in Iraq \& gave him 
``weapons of mass destruction'' to kill
Iranians during the Iran Iraq war out of
fear of fundamentalism. It also gave weapons
\& CIA training to Bin Laden in Afghanistan
to fight them damn commies.
Kuwait, Saudi Arabia gave Saddam money
to do their dirty work during the Iran Iraq war 
\& Kuwait had the nerve to ask a bankrupt Iraq
for the money back after the war, no wonder
Saddam invaded Kuwait, they really ticked him off.
How can we be lovers if we can't make amends,
how can we be lovers if the fighting never ends.
\paragraph
\noindent
Any kind of ``ism'' is born out of ignorance \& fear,
nationalism is a sin, it is
``Pride in the name of love'' the biggest sin of all,
Martin Luther King... tell Bono.
Sinne Fianna Fail, Gerry Adams for Irish president, united Ireland.
Oprah Winfrey for American President,
Oprah if you think you are not the woman for the job
ask yourself do you seriously think you would do a 
worse job than George W. . Make me a sinner,
proud to be Irish, vote with me!
\paragraph
\noindent
The Star Of David is a Swastika, ask any Palestinian.
\paragraph
\noindent
I believe Karma exists, so does empathy, you reap what you sow,
what you give out to the World comes back to you with interest,
treat people like crap \& watch what happens when they get fed up of you.
George W. your lust for oil caused the Twin Towers,
Bin Laden your non functioning kidneys, maybe you deserved them.
Osama, there were no virgins waiting in Heaven for the edjits you
got to crash into the Twin Towers.
Saddam look at the fine mess you got yourself into.
George W. why did you fly all of Bin Laden's family
out of the U.S. while all the rest of the planes
in the U.S. were grounded immediately after the 
Twin Towers disaster?. 
\paragraph
\noindent
Pope Benedict why do you drive in a bulletproof car?, don't you trust God?
Why is the Vatican so wealthy don't you know it is easier
for a rich man to get through the Eye of a Needle than
into Heaven.
\paragraph
\noindent
Al Jizera why don't you do an English
version of the news \& give some balanced
reporting on the European \& U.S. satellite
systems. We need something
other than propaganda. The media
is messing with the heads of Americans
by intermittently telling them there is danger
of an imminent terrorist attack \& next day
there isn't, this headwrecking would give
anybody a mental breakdown.
Isn't it amazing that the Twin Towers
got more news coverage than the millions
of people who lost their lives recently
in Pakistan, the St. Stephens Tsunami Disaster
, the New Orleans flood \& the millions of innocent Iraqis
who have died of cancer owing to George W. Bush
allowing the use of depleted Uranium anti
tank weapons in Iraq, these people have received no
news coverage whatsoever in the western World,
well done George.\\\\
Sincerely
D.J. Barrow.

\chapter{Open letter to anyone interested in space exploration, 
Gerry Ryan, Dave Fanning, Bob Geldof, Bill Gates, Bono,
Larry Ellison,Michael O' Leary, Eddie Jordan, Richard Branson,
Burt Rutan John Mac Carmac, Paul Allen \& Michael Jackson}
\paragraph
\noindent
Hi Bill,Bono, you must be really proud about winning
Time magazine's 2005 people of the year award,
especially seeing as your had such a hard act to follow,
George W. Bush who won the 2004 award for
his efforts in creating world peace?
A question, would you give up all your wealth for true happiness?
\paragraph
\noindent
Bill I know you love Richard Feynman, Porches \& 
used love The Clockwork Orange though I suspect you
consider it a bit childish now, we have a lot in common.
My favourite film is Dangerous Liaisons,
any interest in a Dangerous Liaison with me?
Bill you are worth more than the GDP of many countries.
Bob try to get 99\% of Bill's money off him \& give it to Africa,
he will still be a billionaire anyway \& survive the ``cash rape''.
Make an agreement between Bill \& Bono that if Bono
is man enough to give away 75\% of his wealth Bill will
match it with 99\% they are both stinking rich from my perspective,
lets see if these two really deserved the awards bestowed on them.
\paragraph
\noindent
Bono if you do this like Muhammad Ali you will hammer a lot of respect
into a lot of people, especially politicians looking after their
own backs, by putting your money where your
mouth is you won't need to be wearing shades to be cool,
it certainly will do more for your credibility than making headlines 
by fighting a silly woman in court over a silly \$200 dollar stetson hat.
Don't get me wrong Live Aid \& Live 8 were fantastic
but there is a certain pretentiousness in some almost billionaire
pop stars getting the common man to part with their money
without parting with some of their own.
\paragraph
\noindent
Bill what the hell do you want the money for anyway?,
a safety net in case you go broke?, power?, you can't
take it with you when you die \& you can't eat it
if you go hungry, it's useless,
how can your kids ever learn the value of money
in the neverland detached from reality you have them living in,
you would need to give away 99.999\% get them be
as grounded as your average Joe Soap.
Bob while you are at it sting
the Bushs for some of their personal wealth I'll
bet Michael Moore can calculate their worth to the penny,
if they are slow parting with their money take them to
Africa \& Iraq for a wake up call \& to see the fine mess
they are making of the place there.
\paragraph
\noindent
Bob make sure the money gets to the people most deserving of it
\& that the money doesn't go into some African dictator's hands. 
\paragraph
\noindent
Bob Geldof, Bono, Michael Jackson how would you
like to hold a leg of Live Aid 2 from Mars.
Michael Jackson you are a nice guy.
I heard you were interested in meeting
Martians, we can make the guys who go up in the
scramjet citizens of Mars, would that do you?
\paragraph
\noindent
Larry Ellison I know you love MIGs would you pay
to fly the scramjet?  how much are you willing to pay
help make it happen?, I don't think you would have
the patience for the Mars trip so would some
test flights around Earth do you?
Richard Branson, Burt Rutan any interest in coming closer
to living up to the name Virgin Galactic?
Michael O' Leary CEO of Ryanair have you any interest in keeping
control of finances to make sure the job gets done cheaply?,
Eddie Jordan have you any interest in organizing the advertising?
The only thing I would like painted on the thing myself is a small Swastika
with a Star of David next to it symbolizing peace between
Germans \& Jews.
Gerry Ryan, Dave Fanning can you get Bob Geldof, Bono \& Cmdr. Collins
the NASA Astronaut who recently went up on the Space Shuttle
whom you interviewed recently going so he can get NASA interested,
\& make Live Aid2 a reality.
\paragraph
\noindent
I love Russian Tu-144 jets,
they were made of primitive technology \& were
300 miles an hour faster than Concorde.
If the craft is being built by private enterprise
it would be cheapest to build it in Russia.
While the Americans have their spaceships
in the Smithsonian Museum the Russians have
theirs rotting in the back yards of their launch pads, it's sad.
They Russian space agency would really appreciate the money
provided by private enterprise, they really
deserve a shot to help make this happen.
I would like to see other space agencies
like NASA get involved too.
\paragraph
\noindent
Bill I know you are interested in beating Linux at
it's own game, here is what you do... support Cygwin.
You can already run nearly all the Linux apps on Windows.
Steve Jobs has got Linux engineers flying to MacOS X
in droves because there are about 50 GUI's on Linux
hardly any of them any good except KDE. Windows is safe
your users don't want the headache of learning Linux.
KDE boys your software is far too expensive on Windows.
why don't you make your software MYPL
``pay us what you think the software is worth'',
In an ideal world everything should be under MYPL even food.
If KDE is any good people will pay you for it rather
than see it die. I personally hope that all the open
source GUI developers will stop reinventing the wheel
\& go with KDE \& give a consistent interface to Linux.
Bill I think all software should be sold under MYPL
All my software is officially under GPL but
unofficially I hope to be paid for it. I am a communist
rather than a capitalist unlike yourself who likes
haggling, I couldn't be arsed running around looking
for money off people who really don't want to give it to me,
possibly because they don't think my software is much good anyway
\& chasing ``software pirates'', it wastes too much energy.\\\\
Sincerely,
D.J. Barrow
